      </p>

      <h2>2. Service Description</h2>
      <p>
        Starbloom provides an Edge AI &amp; Automation Orchestration Platform consisting of:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Edge AI Orchestration:</strong> Pre-configured local automation appliances
        running n8n workflows on client-owned hardware.</li>
        <li><strong>24/7 AI Intake Engine:</strong> Conversational AI voice and SMS agents for lead
        capture and qualification.</li>
        <li><strong>Legacy Data Bridge:</strong> Vision-RPA agents that extract data from
        closed-source legacy systems and stream to cloud visualization platforms.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        All platform components are deployed on client-owned hardware. Starbloom provides
        configuration, orchestration, and support services. We do not host, store, or process client
        operational data on our infrastructure.
      </p>

      <h2>3. Private Beta Program</h2>
      <p>
        As of the effective date, all Starbloom platform deployments are conducted through a Private
        Beta Cohort program. Beta participation means:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Pricing, feature availability, and support levels are subject to refinement based on
        cohort feedback.</li>
        <li>Deployment timelines are scheduled by cohort availability and may be subject to queue
        prioritization.</li>
        <li>Beta participants receive priority access to platform updates and direct input into the
        product roadmap.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>4. Deployment Agreements</h2>
      <p>
        Each platform deployment is governed by a separate deployment agreement detailing scope,
        timeline, hardware specifications, integration targets, and support terms. These Terms of
        Service provide the general framework. The deployment agreement controls in the event of any
        conflict.
      </p>

      <h2>5. Client Responsibilities</h2>
      <p>
        Clients are responsible for:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Providing compatible hardware meeting minimum specifications.</li>
        <li>Maintaining network connectivity as required for outbound tunnel operation.</li>
        <li>Securing their own credentials for integrated third-party services (Twilio, Google Cloud,
        Vapi, etc.).</li>
        <li>Reviewing and accepting the terms and privacy policies of any integrated third-party
        services.</li>
        <li>Ensuring compliance with all applicable laws and regulations in their jurisdiction.</li>
      </ul>

